column1: Now more than ever the small businesses in your community need your support! If you’re able to look for online and COVID-19 friendly way to support the entrepreneurs and establishments that are staples in your community. #SmallBizSaturday

While Washington state officials work to stop the alarming spread of COVID-19 in our state Mitch McConnell and President Trump need to stop standing in the way of robust federal relief that is desperately needed. https://t.co/T1YO8M8Zr0

This is the kind of forward-looking strategic planning our federal COVID-19 response has been lacking from the start. It’s an encouraging sign that efforts to #BuildBackBetter are already in the works so the Biden-Harris Administration can hit the ground running on day one. https://t.co/TnO4sBmMge

We must stay vigilant to stop the spread of COVID-19 in Washington state. Please continue to socially distance wear masks limit in-person gatherings and follow public health guidelines. https://t.co/UGTK0Fez74

I’m working to make sure our nation’s response to the COVID-19 crisis including the development of future vaccines is based on science and facts—and not influenced by political interference. https://t.co/SEox1DFBBF

The impact of the coronavirus pandemic has made one thing clear: access to affordable health care is essential. We cannot allow the GOP to reverse our progress on affordable health care in November—at the ballot box or the Supreme Court. https://t.co/02c6N0yFka

We need more leaders in D.C. that will prioritize public health—not politicize critical issues like affordable health care and COVID-19. @DrAlGrossAK is working to flip a crucial seat in Alaska to give working families the Senator they deserve. Join him: https://t.co/WVGntBzkns https://t.co/x8CqDJFtvZ

COVID-19 has only compounded the racial inequities in our health care system that were created by generations of racism & bias. The Senate needs to take action to ensure communities of color have the resources they need to weather this storm & after. https://t.co/CDUfobwoNf

Even now that 200000 Americans have lost their lives from COVID-19 President Trump is continuing to downplay this virus and interfere with the scientists and experts for his own political gain. We desperately need real leadership during this unprecedented public health crisis. https://t.co/GzeaVVy5KL

The Trump Administration’s political influence in our nation’s response to COVID-19 has got to stop. It’s wasting time costing lives and threatening our ability to slow and contain this virus. https://t.co/2OrotDNVQv

We cannot allow the President’s misinformation and meddling to impact our nation’s COVID-19 response when lives and livelihoods are on the line. I will keep pushing this Admin for needed transparency—and I hope my Republican colleagues will do the same.

The wildfire and hazardous smoke conditions are making it even more difficult for families and communities to protect themselves against COVID-19. Stay informed and stay inside. https://t.co/ggB1hHNwBj

When COVID-19 vaccines are available to the public people across the country must be assured that it is based on science and public health not misinformation from the President. https://t.co/QvWH5yNgBx

If we want the public to be confident in future COVID-19 vaccines—which is critical to slowing this virus—we need to be assured that the process wasn’t influenced by political interference and misinformation from President Trump.

I'm hopeful that public pressure on the Senate Republicans and Mitch McConnell will bring them to the table on COVID-19 relief because our communities our neighbors and our families are hurting. https://t.co/XFE4VuG3mt

Read this 👇 deeply-troubling @NYTimes report and then remember it’s been *170 days* since President Trump said we’d soon have zero COVID-19 cases in the U.S.—and Republicans are still fighting to take away your health care.   Vote them all out. https://t.co/IIK6SavTAo

Health care was already one of the most important issues in this election—even before COVID-19. We need to win back the White House & the Senate so we can put a stop to the GOP’s attacks on affordable health care & protections for patients with pre-ex conditions. #ProtectOurCare https://t.co/4NVA6wjn25

Communities of color have been hit especially hard by the COVID-19 pandemic. We need to ensure that Congress’ response to this crisis meaningfully addresses these unequal health and economic impacts. https://t.co/wiMcGSfb51

Ensuring that the distribution & administration of COVID-19 vaccines is done safely effectively and right is a critical step in our fight against this virus—and the public health experts should absolutely be the ones in charge. https://t.co/yir1VXgfL4

We need full transparency about how COVID-19 is impacting state and federal prison systems. I joined @ewarren & @CoryBooker in the fight to require accurate timely reporting of cases. https://t.co/sHpAZhlqfC

Women are some of the people hardest hit by COVID-19 and the related economic crisis. I am pushing for urgent action on issues like child care education & extending unemployment benefits. https://t.co/OyQEF2Qh5e

The families and child care providers I’m talking to desperately need relief—and they need it now. I will keep fighting to make sure this crucial support is included in the next COVID-19 relief package. https://t.co/HXuQKE9HZs
The Senate Republicans' COVID-19 relief proposal is late misguided and completely inadequate. https://t.co/AeWcdwGTnW

I’m with @ewarren. We need to support students and families through this economic crisis and include a student debt cancellation measure in the Senate’s upcoming COVID-19 relief package. https://t.co/F8fq0BS6bF

I'm so glad @JoeBiden is putting child care front & center. We've long had a child care crisis & with COVID-19 putting us at risk of losing ~4.5M slots nationwide it's clear that we need bold long-term solutions to help every family find & afford the child care they need. https://t.co/lccnhrL5Be
The Trump Administration's response to COVID-19 is a disaster. We need to elect leaders this November who will put science and facts above politics and profit.

The COVID-19 pandemic has made the student debt crisis so much worse & Secretary Betsy DeVos can’t even be bothered to do the bare minimum of her job and help & support struggling student loan borrowers. Our students deserve better. https://t.co/rJ76RkFsW1

Why is the Trump Administration sitting on $14 billion of approved funds to expand COVID-19 testing and contact tracing? These funds should be disbursed to our communities immediately. https://t.co/q8wSEIKlex
We are still in the middle of a pandemic. Please continue to social distance wear face masks wash your hands and follow local public health guidance.  https://t.co/UliEzYx0bB

Secretary Betsy DeVos is continuing to turn her back on our students with this outrageous rule that will block undocumented students from receiving needed coronavirus relief grants. https://t.co/twHlYpeNVN

Once again Secretary Betsy DeVos is an abject failure when it comes to standing with students. She must reverse this rule that bars millions of college students from receiving the COVID-19 relief they need. https://t.co/FQ4iHxOpkX

Congress needs to make a massive investment in our schools to help them adapt to and recover from the COVID-19 crisis and to prevent further inequities in our education system. https://t.co/4t8WsiaaLA

In many ways the coronavirus pandemic has made the inequities in our education system even worse. We must work now to address the widening student achievement gap caused by this public health crisis. https://t.co/FvZSLrujT4

As colleges reopen we all must be focused on ensuring Black students & other students of color who are already facing disproportionate impacts from the COVID-19 pandemic get the support and access to resources they need to keep their education on track. https://t.co/IijSAQQhpo

President Trump’s national COVID-19 testing plan is inadequate and disappointing. The President should be leading on testing rather than denying the truth and shifting responsibility to states. https://t.co/gy7gYI32Jf

Secretary DeVos is working to rob our public schools of the COVID-19 relief they need instead redirecting funds to private schools. We simply can’t let these outrageous actions stand. https://t.co/yKhmqJyhJu

The Trump Administration’s lazy response to the serious impacts of this pandemic makes clear that they would rather ignore how the coronavirus is impacting communities of color than deal with it. This is totally unacceptable. https://t.co/UPmK0Gdq5Q

We still need a national plan to make COVID-19 testing fast free & everywhere in order to safely reopen our communities—and every day the Trump Administration continues to delay is more time our families & communities are at risk.

While families and small businesses struggle to get by Majority Leader Mitch McConnell is calling for a “pause” on any further COVID-19 relief packages in the Senate. There is no excuse for inaction during this pandemic. Add your name now if you agree: https://t.co/knzFlwqWqC

Families schools and small businesses across the nation need an aggressive transparent  plan from the Trump Administration to address our COVID-19 testing needs. The lack of national leadership is only making this crisis worse. https://t.co/IpBogLisUm

The COVID-19 pandemic has only deepened the digital divide for students workers seniors and more. I will keep pushing the Senate to expand broadband access to all of our communities and fighting for #DigitalEquityNow. https://t.co/hlX9zSQIho

Too many families were already struggling to navigate the child care crisis and the impacts of the coronavirus pandemic and response are only making the crisis worse. I’m going to keep working in Congress to help guarantee high-quality #ChildCare4All.

When I asked Dr. Fauci about the consequences of cities and states opening too soon he warned of the serious impacts—including spikes that could lead to additional COVID-19 outbreaks. https://t.co/SjxYRrq2xh

We all want to see an end to this crisis. But we need smart federal leadership to help get us through it starting with a plan to ensure COVID-19 testing is fast free and widely available. https://t.co/gWu114P45i
We need to do more to ensure that students and schools have the support that they need to navigate the coronavirus pandemic. https://t.co/AqYg8a6pT1

Today is #NationalNursesDay—a time to celebrate the nurses who work so hard every day to keep us healthy and safe. This year as we navigate the COVID-19 pandemic we are even more grateful for the selfless sacrifices our nurses are making to protect our public health.

The child care crisis in Washington state and across the country has only worsened during the #COVID19 pandemic. Congress must do more to support working families -- I’ll keep fighting for affordable high-quality #ChildCare4All. https://t.co/uqQSZYUpuF

Any future coronavirus relief packages must include immigrant communities many who are working on the frontlines of this pandemic in our hospitals farms grocery stores and more. https://t.co/uEvlgWQLVY

As the Trump Administration moves to reopen federal agencies we need real answers on the plans in place to keep federal employees healthy and safe during the COVID-19 pandemic. https://t.co/8YsRpycDDb

Public health officials have been clear that we need to significantly increase COVID-19 testing before we can safely reopen. The White House’s attempts continue to fall short but I’ll keep pushing for the progress we need. https://t.co/JUa3PSjohU

The White House’s testing blueprint is deeply insufficient. I will keep pushing for the serious and aggressive action we need to ramp up coronavirus testing & address this crisis. https://t.co/64YhQvy2Hb
We must listen to the public health experts and work to increase coronavirus testing before taking steps to safely reopen our country and economy. https://t.co/NqEsuppdv9

Senate Democrats fought hard to ensure the latest relief package provides funding for a major expansion of coronavirus testing along with urgently needed support for our hospitals and targeted assistance to truly small businesses. https://t.co/lLTe9FVTEJ

Extreme politicians are using the COVID-19 public health crisis as an opportunity to try to enforce their dangerous anti-abortion agenda. This is cruel and dangerous. We must keep fighting to stop these attacks on our #reprorights. https://t.co/CMvzpWOep6

I fought to successfully ensure the newest COVID-19 relief bill included funding to invest in and expand testing along with urgently needed support for our hospitals and small businesses. https://t.co/jSKu1FHWv5

President Trump is trying to distract everyone from his failed leadership to address the coronavirus crisis by pushing his harmful anti-immigrant agenda. Instead he should be focused on addressing this crisis and expanding testing. https://t.co/mnXqKKkQJS
I am going to keep doing everything I can to make sure that Washington state gets what it needs from the other Washington to address and recover from the #COVID19 crisis. https://t.co/bYsh707fEV

Before we can even consider lifting social distance requirements & getting back to normal we need a major expansion of COVID-19 testing that is available to everyone everywhere. https://t.co/amSS3eLXJZ

The COVID-19 pandemic is highlighting racial disparities and inequality that already exist in our communities and health care system--which makes it absolutely critical that we ensure every patient can access the treatment they need. https://t.co/zqnE22dHpb
As the COVID-19 public health crisis continues organizations supporting those affected by this pandemic need our help. Here is more information if you are able to help. https://t.co/XRDwwCqY3i

Abortion is essential health care — and it’s cruel that extreme politicians are using the COVID-19 pandemic as an excuse to undermine or restrict our fundamental reproductive rights. https://t.co/YQnqFXUZK4

Please continue to listen to the experts and stay home unless absolutely necessary. We all must do our part to slow the spread of COVID-19. https://t.co/JUSXxC3nDe
In addition to continuing to stay home social distance and wash your hands often the latest CDC recommendations now include wearing a cloth mask when you leave your home. https://t.co/RklUq7vvkT

With the coronavirus pandemic putting a major strain on our food banks in Washington state Gov. @JayInslee is launching the #WAFoodFund to help feed families in need during this crisis. Learn more about how you can help. https://t.co/vuXxrBFxva

President Trump just removed the inspector general tasked with overseeing $2 trillion in coronavirus emergency funds. This is outrageous and this President must be held accountable. https://t.co/di7e3JnobX
Washington state is a leader in voting by mail and a model that other states can and should emulate — especially with the uncertainty of the coronavirus crisis.  https://t.co/rRBAV6Sfxt

We must keep fighting until every nurse and health care worker on the front lines of this pandemic has access to the personal protective equipment they need to protect themselves from COVID-19. https://t.co/k8KHakxKNU

We cannot retreat from the fight to stop the spread of coronavirus in Washington state. We can save lives in this pandemic — but we must stay strong and continue to stay home. https://t.co/eW40nVcSzM
Anti-abortion extremists using the COVID-19 crisis to further their harmful agenda is just plain cruel. We must keep fighting to stop these reckless attacks. https://t.co/r7ChDqS64Y

We must continue to listen to public health experts and practice social distancing. Even if you aren’t sick follow the guidelines to help #flattenthecurve and slow the spread of the coronavirus. https://t.co/6x4XqjS34k

The coronavirus pandemic is only making the child care crisis worse. We passed critical support for child care in the Senate package — and I will keep fighting for affordable #ChildCare4All. https://t.co/ckfV2mXU3C

There is no doubt that we are facing a public health emergency. Here are the 3 things you need to know about the coronavirus pandemic right now.

The President has said the coronavirus will go away and that his White House’s response has been perfect. His team told people to turn off their TVs to avoid the news. We need serious leadership not denial and downplaying. https://t.co/FapiitMJXw
